miscellaneous tools for molecular biology.

** Commands

get_genbank: get GenBank file from ncbi.
geneview: render overview image of gene sequence, annotation
seqview: render overview image of sequence, primers, bisulfite sequence results.
tssview: count the number of tss tags of specific genes, by DBTSS
bisearch: design primer based on primer3 algorithm.
primers: calculate primer properties
virtualpcr: PCR primer alignment tool using bowtie

** Install
python setup.py install

** Mac OS X, homebrew and python Environment

*** Installing Brew's python
http://penandpants.com/2012/02/24/install-python/
https://github.com/mxcl/homebrew/wiki/Homebrew-and-Python

% which python
/usr/bin/python
% python --version
Python 2.7.1
% brew install python
% which python
/usr/local/bin/python
% sudo easy_install virtualenv
% virtualenv --version
1.8.2
% which virtualenv
/usr/local/share/python/virtualenv
% pip install numpy

% brew install gfortran
% pip install scipy
  --> failed. ;-P

*** virtualenv setup

% virtualenv env
New python executable in env/bin/python
Installing setuptools............done.
Installing pip...............done.
% source env/bin/activate   
(env)% python setup.py develop 
  --> numpy compile failed ;-PPP
(env)% pip install numpy
  --> success
(env)% python setup.py develop 
...
Using /Users/mizuy/projects/seqtool/env/lib/python2.7/site-packages
Finished processing dependencies for seqtool==0.1.1

** databases

for gene tables
see: make dbload

for dbtss
http://dbtss.hgc.jp/

use bed files of 'liftover' folders.
ex. ftp://ftp.hgc.jp/pub/hgc/db/dbtss/dbtss_ver8/hg19_liftover/TSSseq/bed/adult-tissue/

** building boost
no user-config.bjam required.

% cd boost_1_52_0
% ./boostrap.sh --with-toolset=clang
% ./b2 toolset=clang cxxflags="-std=c++11 -stdlib=libc++" linkflags="-stdlib=libc++" install
% clang++ -Wall -std=c++0x -stdlib=libc++ -L/usr/local/lib -I/usr/local/include -O1 -lboost_program_options c/bisearch.cpp c/main.cpp -o bin/bisearch

You must link boost_program_options

** matplot
git clone https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib.git
cd matplotlib
python setup.py build
sudo python setup.py install


